							"score": 5,
							"reviewDescription": "This game is criminally underrated:\n- it is narrated by Patrick Stewart\n- it is visually beautiful and poetic\n- it is narrated by Patrick Stewart\n- the puzzles are nice, playing with shadows, portals and gravity, hard enough to be challenging but never frustrating and highly rewarding when completed\n- it is narrated by Patrick Stewart\n- the story is simple and not without plot holes but mysterious and moving - you really get attached to Lorna, you gradually discover what really happened, and it is overall satisfying\n- it is narrated by Patrick Stewart\n- the music is very nice, the end credit song in particular is haunting.\n\nOverall, this is typically what I expect from VR: being transported to an impossible world with impossible physics that however feels real, and a story you feel involved in.\n\nThis game deserves wider recognition. Congrats to the devs! I want more!\n\nOh, and did I mention it is narrated by Patrick Stewart?",
